Cecil F. DOUGHTY, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Rose BECHER, Defendant-Appellee, and David Langer, Defendant. No. 208. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit March 3, 1941. Albert Bonynge, of New York City (John F. X. Finn, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. John J. Kirwan, of New York City (James J. McLoughlin and Robert F. White, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
